    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-05-22T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-05-22T18:00:00-05:00" n="199"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d199">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.74/5–2245: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the United States Representative in Bulgaria</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Barnes</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-05-22T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 22, 1945—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>138. With reference to the Department’s telegram to Schoenfeld,<note n="51"
                        xml:id="d199fn1">No. 43, May 22, 7 p.m., to Budapest, <ref target="#pg_819"
                            >p. 819</ref>. H. F. Arthur Schoenfeld was U. S. Representative in
                        Hungary.</note> repeated to you as no. 139, you may, unless you see
                    objections to such a procedure at just this juncture, indicate the willingness
                    of this Government to entertain any proposals the Bulgarian Government may wish
                    to make regarding the sending of Bulgarian representative to this country. You
                    should make it clear that such a representative would not be accredited
                    officially to this Government and that his <pb facs="0232" n="220"
                        xml:id="pg_220"/> presence here would in no sense imply a resumption of
                    diplomatic relations between the two countries.</p>
                <p>Sent to Sofia; repeated to Bucharest and Budapest.<note n="52" xml:id="d199fn2"
                        >As Nos. 259 and 42, respectively.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
